This is showing how to join 2 mbrick files (top.md and bottom.md) to get a geo file via joint.mbl.
The result is the geo file or for easier viewing a ghost script file (Tz000.eps)
The comments in the plotpar and md files do not need to start with # but it is easier for me at least to see where they start.
plotpar and md files have the comment at the end of the commands on that line.